---
export const prerender = true;

import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <h2>1. Data Sovereignty &amp; Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    FactLockCam is your private vault with a sovereign zero-knowledge local lock. Only you hold the
    keys—we cannot access your unencrypted files. We do not track, profile, or monetize your personal
    information. Our systems are designed so that we never have access to your unencrypted files,
    cryptographic keys, or private data.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Authentication and Identity</h2>
  <p>
    Your email address is used exclusively to generate a unique identity record. This enables you to
    anchor digital certificates to the Polygon blockchain without centralized account management
    beyond authentication. We do not use your email for marketing, and it is never shared with third
    parties.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Zero-Knowledge Architecture</h2>
  <p>
    FactLockCam operates on a strict zero-knowledge principle. All cryptographic operations and
    file encryptions occur locally on your device before any data transmission. We cannot see,
    access, or recover your files or private keys. Your unencrypted data never leaves your device
    except when you explicitly export or share it.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Local Encryption &amp; Secure Storage</h2>
  <p>
    Assets are encrypted on-device using AES-GCM before being stored in the protected archive on
    your device. FactLockCam manages cryptographic keys using the device&apos;s native hardware
    security modules (iOS Keychain / Secure Enclave where available). These keys are never
    transmitted to or stored on our servers.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Public Ledger Integrity</h2>
  <p>
    When you certify a file, only a mathematical hash (SHA-256) is sent to the Polygon blockchain.
    Your filenames, identity, and actual file contents are never exposed on the public ledger. The
    ledger serves only as an immutable timestamped proof of the file&apos;s integrity.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data Protection and AI</h2>
  <p>
    FactLockCam does not share your data, files, or identity with third-party AI or machine learning
    services. All file hashing and processing are performed locally on your hardware to support
    maximum data privacy.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Non-Custodial Security Policy</h2>
  <p>
    Because FactLockCam is non-custodial and operates on zero-knowledge principles, we do not store
    your encryption keys or credentials. Consequently, we cannot reset passwords or recover
    accounts. Users are solely responsible for maintaining access to their credentials and backing
    up their encrypted assets.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Location Data</h2>
  <p>
    When you grant location permission, FactLockCam displays live GPS coordinates on the camera
    viewfinder for forensic metadata capture. Location readings are embedded in your local capture
    workflow and are not uploaded to our servers unless you explicitly include them in an exported
    proof bundle.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a href="/legal/privacy-policy.pdf">Download PDF version</a> (fallback for reviewers without
    JavaScript).
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
